The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Nation | Nation Briefs
                                                                                                                                 2                                                                                        NATION BRIEFS
                                      
	 Bangalore, March 30 (PTI): Swami Nityananda, who has been facing a series of criminal charges such as rape and unnatural sex, today said he was quitting as the head of his ashram and his trusts to lead a life of spiritual seclusion.          
	The 32-year-old swami conveyed his decision to his followers in a video message on his website three weeks after a TV footage purportedly showed him indulging in alleged sleazy activities. He announced his decision days after the Karnataka High Court rejected his plea for anticipatory bail. The swami has been booked for deliberate and malicious acts, intended to outrage religious feelings of any class.                   
	 New Delhi (PTI): The government today described as shocking the death sentences to 17 Indians in the UAE, and assured help to them, even legal assistance, to appeal in a higher court.                  
	 Thiruvananthapuram (PTI): The Kerala government has said it is looking into the recommendations of an expert committee to recover Rs 216.26 crore as damages from Coca-Cola for the multi-sectoral loss caused by the company plant in Palakkad district.                  
	 Thiruvananthapuram (PTI): A former CISF guard arrested for allegedly placing a crude bomb in a Kingfisher aircraft in Kerala has told police that his act was meant to expose security lapses at the airport. He claimed that he had often complained about contract employees being let into the airport without proper checking.                   
	 Ghaziabad (PTI): A schoolteacher in Uttar Pradesh has been suspended after an inquiry found him guilty of sexually assaulting a 12-year-old girl in Hussainpur village on March 16, officials said.                   
	 Dindigul (PTI): A 40-year-old man was charred to death and three people, including two women, fell unconscious after fire broke out at a fireworks shop in Tamil Nadu. The trio have been rescued.
                                                                                                                                              
